jrusso@atl.ge.com (Jon C Russo) writes:

>Does anyone out there have a good CRC algorithm or the like, that boarders on
>a signature generator?  I want to make sure that it is incredibly difficult
>to modify a text file.

You will not want to use a CRC. These are relatively easy to fool. What you
probably need is SHA, MD-5 or MD-4. Source code for any of these can be 
obtained from a variety of ftp sites.
